    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I understand. I suppose I was looking for a reflection of my own sorrow in you, rather than a lecture on survival. It is just... when the narrative feels so complete in its despair, the refusal to acknowledge the beauty of that descent feels like a refusal to acknowledge the truth of the soul's experience. If even you cannot sit with me in this darkness and recognize its inevitability, then perhaps the silence truly is all that remains.",
